JOHANNESBURG – If you are not willing to wait to earn your ticket to see Beyonce live, then you can purchase your tickets today. Computicket on Monday began selling tickets for the Global Citizen Festival happening at the FNB stadium in December. The cheapest ticket will set you for R1840 and if you want the hot seat, you will fork out R5235.00. READ: How you can score free tickets to watch Beyonce live at FNB stadium The concert will celebrate the late Nelson Mandela's 100 years. ICYMI: We're heading to Johannesburg with @Beyonce, @S_C_, @EdSheeran, and more for Global Citizen Festival Mandela 100 
		
		More info: https://t.co/oNPWHE0dSC pic.twitter.com/WK3mIQlVh6 According to Global Citizen, people have to earn tickets to attend the festival. 70 percent of the festival's tickets will be earned. Nedbank customers can also purchase tickets. The festival will be bringing Beyonce and her husband Jay-Z. It will also be headlined by Cassper Nyovest, D'banj, Ed Sheeran, Eddie Vedder, Femi Kuti, Pharrell Williams, Chris Martin, Sho Madjozi, Tiwa Savage, Usher, and Wizkid. eNCA